[h1]Changelog[/h1]

[h2]v0.8.0 — 2026-03-18 (Preview Release)[/h2]
[b]Screen stack architecture, 3-column layout, power consumption[/b]

[u]Screen Stack Architecture[/u]
[list]
[*] New POS_API — public screen registration with validation, guards, and extension support
[*] New POS_Registry — central screen + menu category storage with filtered queries
[*] New POS_MenuBuilder — dynamic menu generation from registry (replaces hardcoded menus)
[*] shouldShow / canOpen guard system — screens declare access requirements
[*] Declarative requires: connected, minSignal, bands — enforced automatically
[*] onEnter / onExit lifecycle hooks for screen state management
[*] Breadcrumb navigation path displayed in content header
[*] Dot-namespaced screen IDs (pos.main, pos.bbs.operations, etc.)
[*] Menu categories with sortOrder for clean hierarchy
[*] tryRegisterScreen() for third-party extension safety
[*] MainMenu + BBS Hub now generate menus dynamically from the registry
[/list]

[u]3-Column Terminal Layout[/u]
[list]
[*] NavPanel (left sidebar) — persistent navigation with signal indicator + menu items
[*] ContextPanel (right sidebar) — screen-specific detail inspector
[*] Responsive: ContextPanel auto-collapses below 900px window width
[*] Stencil clipping on all panels prevents content bleed-over
[*] 5 screens provide context data: Operations, Deliveries, Investments, Negotiate, BBS
[*] Sandbox toggles: EnableNavPanel, EnableContextPanel
[/list]

[u]Terminal Power Consumption[/u]
[list]
[*] Desktop terminals consume generator fuel while open (0.15%/min default)
[*] Grid power is free — drain only applies when grid is off
[*] Terminal auto-closes with message on power failure
[*] Connection blocked when desktop has no electricity
[*] Cross-mod drain detection — highest rate wins, no stacking
[*] Sandbox: TerminalPowerDrainRate (0 = disabled)
[/list]

[u]Code Quality[/u]
[list]
[*] POS_Constants — centralised cross-file constants (commands, screen IDs, item types, modData keys)
[*] POS_TerminalWidgets — shared layout helpers (initLayout, drawHeader, drawFooter, defaultDestroy)
[*] All magic numbers and strings extracted to named constants across 35+ files
[*] 5 new sandbox options from magic number audit (delivery expiry, scan radii, investment variance/floor)
[*] safeGetText() canonicalised in PhobosLib (was duplicated 13 times)
[*] ~200 lines of boilerplate eliminated via shared helpers
[/list]

[h2]v0.7.0 — 2026-03-18[/h2]
[b]AZAS dual-band, frequency validation, signal strength[/b]

[list]
[*] Hard dependency on AZAS Frequency Index — dynamic per-world frequencies
[*] Dual-band registration: POSnet_Operations (amateur) + POSnet_Tactical (military)
[*] Radio must be tuned to correct frequency to connect
[*] Desktop computers display POSnet frequencies for reference
[*] Band determines content access: amateur = Tier I-II, tactical = Tier III-IV
[*] Signal strength system: inverse square law from radio TransmitRange
[*] Signal gates access below threshold + scales rewards 50-100%
[*] 3 sandbox options: EnableSignalStrength, SignalReferencePower, MinSignalThreshold
[*] Street addresses via PhobosLib_Address.resolveAddress()
[*] [MAP] button on active missions opens PZ world map at target location
[*] Retroactive building + mailbox scan on first mod load (250-tile radius)
[/list]

[h2]v0.6.0 — 2026-03-18[/h2]
[b]BBS hub, cancellation, negotiation, pagination[/b]

[list]
[*] BBS hub sub-menu — Investments, Operations, Courier under one roof
[*] Mission cancellation at any stage — Tier I free, Tiers II-IV scale upward
[*] Negotiation system — haggle reward/deadline before accepting
[*] Reputation-weighted success (30-85%) with max 3 attempts
[*] PhobosLib_Pagination widget in BBS, Operations, Deliveries screens
[*] replaceCurrent() avoids back-stack pollution for pagination
[*] Investment detail view with accept/decline
[*] Delivery context menu for package pickup/dropoff
[*] Recon scanner with photograph → field report pipeline
[*] Unified reputation framework with 5 tiers (0-2500)
[*] 4 crafting categories: recon photography, field reporting
[/list]

[h2]v0.5.0 — 2026-03-18[/h2]
[b]Portable computer, themes, terminal sizing[/b]

[list]
[*] Portable Computer — 10 kg, rare world loot, battery drains while terminal open
[*] 4 colour themes: Classic Green, Amber, Cool White, IBM Blue
[*] 4 font sizes: Small, Medium, Code, Large
[*] Font-scale-with-window option (independent of PZ settings)
[*] Terminal window resizable with minimum 720x780
[/list]

[h2]v0.3.0 — 2026-03-18[/h2]
[b]Boot sequence + resizable windows[/b]

[list]
[*] DOS-style boot animation with typewriter character reveal on first terminal open per world-load
[*] Terminal window now resizable via drag handle (compatible with "Resize Any Window" mod)
[*] Click anywhere during boot to skip to operations view
[*] Boot animation speed scales with game speed multiplier
[/list]

[h2]v0.2.0 — 2026-03-18[/h2]
[b]Core gameplay loop + terminal UI[/b]

[list]
[*] Retro CRT-style terminal UI — green monospace text on dark background with scanline effect
[*] Physical setup: right-click any radio near a vanilla desktop computer to connect
[*] "Connect to POSnet" context menu on world-placed and inventory radios
[*] Connection validation: checks radio power, on/off state, and desktop computer proximity
[*] Server-to-client operation delivery via OnServerCommand
[*] 5 built-in starter missions
[*] Welcome guide popup explaining setup and usage
[/list]

[h2]v0.1.0 — 2026-03-18[/h2]
[b]Initial scaffold[/b]

[list]
[*] POSnet radio channel registration at configurable frequency
[*] Procedural mission generation from registered templates
[*] 5 mission categories
[*] 4 difficulty levels: Easy, Medium, Hard, Critical
[*] Extensible completion detector with item_acquire built-in checker
[*] Player-side operation log with persistence in modData
[*] Server-side timed broadcast system
[*] 6 sandbox options
[*] CI pipeline with 9 automated checks
[/list]
